This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel approach for video segmentation based on a new video representation. The paper also mentions the use of a probabilistic model and clustering algorithm, which are commonly used techniques in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with video data and proposes a new representation for it. 

The use of clustering algorithms and probabilistic models suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with spatiotemporal relationships among trajectories, which is a common topic in computer graphics.
